'''Acetrax''' is a [[video on demand]] company which was founded in the UK and Switzerland and incorporated as a Swiss company in Zürich in 2006<ref>{{Citation |url=http://archive.iptv-news.com/iptv_news/november_2011/acetrax_the_digital_media_industry_is_completely_back-to-front |title=IPTV News |work= |publisher=Informa Telecoms and Media |accessdate=June 3, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120830231307/http://archive.iptv-news.com/iptv_news/november_2011/acetrax_the_digital_media_industry_is_completely_back-to-front |archivedate=August 30, 2012 }}</ref> and which was bought by [[Sky (UK and Ireland)|Sky]].<ref>{{Citation | url = http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tech/news/a379753/sky-acquires-acetrax-as-it-prepares-for-now-tv-launch.html | title = Sky acquires Acetrax as it prepares for NOW TV launch | work = Digital Spy | publisher = Digital Spy | accessdate = June 3, 2012 }}</ref> The company provides over-the-top (OTT) content in Europe, for [[Smart TV|connected TVs]]. They claim to have their contents on TVs in 282 million households, in 48 countries.<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www5.acetrax.com/about-us.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001031301/http://www5.acetrax.com/about-us.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=October 1, 2011 |title=Focused on Europe |work=About us |publisher=Acetrax |accessdate=June 3, 2012 }}</ref> It is understood that Sky's acquisition of Acetrax in May 2012 will provide the Sky customers who do not currently subscribe to pay TV - with films and music. The move seen as part of the satellite broadcaster's move into the internet TV market.
The gross assets of Acetrax stood at £2.3 million as of December 31, 2011, according to Sky.<ref>{{Citation | url = http://www.cable.co.uk/news/sky-acquires-acetrax-on-demand-streaming-service-801357878/ | title = Sky acquires Acetrax on-demand streaming service | work = Cable | publisher = Cable (Existent Ltd) | accessdate = November 30, 2010 }}</ref>
Acetrax ceased operations as of June 21, 2013.<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.acetrax.com/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050208154336/http://acetrax.com/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=February 8, 2005 |title=Acetrax announce end of operations |accessdate=May 21, 2013 }}</ref>
==Apps== As well as video on demand, Acetrax has also created an [[Mobile app|app]] which is embedded in phones such as [[Samsung]], [[LG]], [[Panasonic]], [[Toshiba]], [[Grundig]].
